## When to Use WebSockets

**Use WebSockets for:**
- Real-time notifications
- Live chat/messaging
- Collaborative editing
- Live updates (new comments, likes, etc.)
- Presence indicators (who's online)
- Typing indicators
- Live dashboards

**Don't use WebSockets for:**
- Simple form submissions (use Turbo Streams)
- One-way updates (use Turbo Streams)
- Infrequent updates (use polling)

